 2.2. Semantic Layer (dbt)
 
 -   **Overview:** The dbt project lives in `warehouse/` and uses DuckDB by default. It reads the warmed CSVs from `data/cache/` to produce the semantic models used by the API.
+
+    **Important env flags (defaults shown):**
+    - `WAREHOUSE_ENABLED` (default `1`) — when set to `0`, the API falls back to static CSV/JSON inputs. See `services/api/settings.py`.
+    - `LEGO_BASELINE_STATIC` (default `1`) — when true, the LEGO baseline is read from `data/cache/lego_baseline_{year}.json`; set to `0` to force warehouse reads.
+
+    These flags determine whether the API reads live dbt models or cached JSON.
@@
